article.headline: Middle Tennessee 72, Florida Atlantic 68
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Kevin Kanaskie scored 19 points to lead Middle Tennessee to a 72-68 win over Florida Atlantic Wednesday. Florida Atlantic (7-9, 3-3 Sun Belt Conference) was up 32-29 at the end of the first half, but Middle Tennessee (7-9, 3-3) came back in the second. Middle Tennessee's Kyle Young scored 13 points, Nigel Johnson scored 13 and Theryn Hudson scored 10. Carlos Monroe scored 17 points for Florida Atlantic. DeAndre Rice scored 15 points, Jeff Parmer scored 12 and Paul Graham scored 11. Middle Tennessee hit half of its 3-point attempts, 61.9 percent of its field goal attempts and 73.9 percent of its free throws.
